New Records: Rookie Spencer Schwellenbach started against Minnesota rookie Simeon Woods Richardson, which marked the most combined letters in the last names of a starting pitching matchup in major league history with 28 letters.
Key Match Events: Matt Olson drove in the go-ahead run on a fielder's choice.
Travis d'Arnaud added an RBI single.
Ramón Laureano put the game away with a two-run double.
Michael Harris returned to the starting lineup and hit his eighth homer of the year.
Marcell Ozuna added two hits, including a two-run double.
Pierce Johnson struck out Matt Wallner with the tying run at first to end the game.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Twins' RHP Joe Ryan was transferred to the 60-day injured list and won't pitch again in the regular season.
